title: Fall Fury
description: The first Annual Fall Fury race begins October 17th and 18th. This race will feature the highest quality that Southern Utah has to offer. There will be Short Track, Downhill, and Cross country. This is also going to be the Collegiate State Championship for Utah
course: The Cross Country course is going to be an intermediate technical trail. About 1000 ft of climbing with a 6 mile loop. The Trail will go up and down Zen trail and come out on the double track road and repeat with some categories. The Down hill will be shuttled up the Zen Mesa and come down on some rocky DH fun. The Short track will loop the power plant and will be very fast and very enjoyable. Start times will be listed on rapidcyclingracing.com
registration: Registration will be done on our website rapidcyclingracing.com
notes: Start times and Categories are subject to change as field sizes get bigger.
directions: Take the Dixie Drive I-15 exit in St. George and turn west. Head down that street and turn left at Canyon View Road, heading uphill toward the Green Valley Spa. (If you reach a "Green Valley Market" with gas pumps, you just passed it. Turn around and backtrack to the second road on your right.) Drive past the spa onto dirt at the end of the road. Turn right at the top of the mesa, then immediately left to drive down into the deep valley. Head for the big road that goes up the bluff, on the right side of The Gap -- the sandstone canyon. But just before that road starts to climb you will see the event on the left.
